{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ca906fec-2cdd-41f5-ae04-956d370908c7","content":"Here's what to do:\n\n1. **Update packages** — replace `xunit.runner.visualstudio` with `xunit.runner.mtp`:\n   ```xml\n   <!-- Remove -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.visualstudio\" Version=\"...\" />\n\n   <!-- Add -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.mtp\" Version=\"2.9.3\" />\n   ```\n\n2. **Enable MTP** in your project file:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n3. **Run tests** the same way:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n\nKey notes:\n- `xunit.runner.mtp` must match your `xunit` package version (2.9.3).\n- With MTP, your test project compiles to an **executable** (not a DLL), so you can also run it directly.\n- Remove `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` if present — it's not needed with MTP.\n- If you use `dotnet test`, the `TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport` property ensures compatibility with the `dotnet test` CLI.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c5d6fd40-3dbf-408f-8204-d7bf3ae02be5","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest runner to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration path.","outputTokens":363,"requestId":"67E9:247AEF:29C4845:2E0D543:69FD3422"},"id":"0132c51d-689c-4ec2-81e7-f7ba0c41f0ea","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:54:02.758Z","parentId":"b31f4d2f-a9ec-4695-b282-496c02874c09"}
